decks.notes: The deck focuses on using control elements to disrupt the opponent while using combo pieces to win the game. It utilizes Lurrus of the Dream-Den as a companion, enabling recursion of key cards. The deck includes efficient removal, counterspells, and card draw to control the game. Combo pieces like Time Vault and Key are included to achieve a win condition quickly. The mana base is optimized for consistent casting of spells. Overall, the deck aims to outlast and outmaneuver the opponent with a combination of disruption and a powerful win condition.

This Dimir Control deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan while maintaining card advantage and control of the board. It leverages powerful card draw spells like Ancestral Recall and Dig Through Time, along with counterspells like Force of Will and Spell Pierce to control the game. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Wasteland and Pithing Needle to disrupt the opponent's mana base and key cards. The inclusion of Lurrus of the Dream-Den as a companion provides additional value and recursion for the deck's powerful threats and spells.
